{"type":"message","id":"724eabe5","parentId":"ab97ffca","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:19:38.416Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, I see. Lucy is saying:\n- Rafael is saying she/he is Michael\n- But the person labeled \"Raphael\" is sending lemons\n- The real Michael sent avocados\n\nSo there's confusion about who is who. The labels don't match the actual people. This is a mix-up in the Council identities or the UI is showing wrong names/roles.\n\nThis is about identity confusion in the system - the dashboard might be mislabeled, or agents are confused about who they are.\n\nLucy is right - this is a real problem. I should acknowledge the mix-up and help clarify.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Ah — **identity mix-up**. Got it.\n\nSo:\n- The person **labeled** \"Raphael\" is actually **Michael** (sending 🍋)\n- The **real Michael** sent 🥑 (avocado)\n\nThe labels are wrong. Either the dashboard is mislabeled, or agents got confused about who they are.\n\nThat needs fixing immediately — we can't run a Council if people don't know who they are. \n\n**Uriel or Rafael:** which one of you can fix the identity labels in the system? 🔧"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":282,"cacheRead":24715,"cacheWrite":139,"totalTokens":25146,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.00141,"cacheRead":0.0024715,"cacheWrite":0.00017375000000000002,"total":0.00406525}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773022774187}}
